        <abstract> 
<p><hi rend="italic">Bombus mastrucatus</hi>, an alpine bee, conforms to his observations that <hi rend="italic">B. terrestris</hi> breaks open the flowers of <hi rend="italic">Trifolium pratense</hi>. However, in the Alps, <hi rend="italic">B. terrestris</hi> does not behave this way.</p>  
<p><hi rend="italic">Gentiana</hi> species are adapted to lepidopteran cross-fertilisation.</p> 
        </abstract>
